VIM on Rails. My dot vim to develop app using Ruby or Ruby on Rails

Usage:
1. Download to your home directory and rename to .vim/
2. Create symbolic link to .vim/.vimrc
% cd ~
% ln -s .vim/.vimrc .vimrc


Plugins:
1. NERD_tree
2. rails
3. SnipMate
4. surround
5. endwise
6. haml

Example:
% vim example.txt

Shorcuts in command mode:
1. Press Shift + Tab to toggle NERD_tree
2. Press i on NERD_tree to open below current file
3. ctrl+h = left tab
4. ctrl+j = down tab
5. ctrl+k = right
6. ,p = copy from clipboard

Available colorscheme:
1. railscasts (default)
2. rdark
3. golden
4. twilight
5. twilight2
6. vividchalk
